# API Endpoints â€“ Book Model

## List All Books
GET /books/
- Returns a list of all books.
- No authentication required.

## Create Book
POST /books/
- Creates a new book.
- Authentication required.
- Required fields: title, author, published_date, isbn, pages.

## Retrieve Book by ID
GET /books/<id>/
- Returns details of a specific book.
- No authentication required.

## Update Book
PUT /books/<id>/
- Updates all fields of a book.
- Authentication required.

## Delete Book
DELETE /books/<id>/
- Deletes a book.
- Authentication required.

# Filtering, Searching, and Ordering

## Filtering
Use query parameters to filter books:
- GET /books/?title=Some%20Title
- GET /books/?author=John%20Doe
- GET /books/?published_date=2024-01-01

## Searching
Use `search` parameter for partial matches:
- GET /books/?search=django
- GET /books/?search=vincent

## Ordering
Use `ordering` parameter to sort:
- GET /books/?ordering=title
- GET /books/?ordering=-published_date
- GET /books/?ordering=pages
